377	    /// - `end`: The end offset of the match
378	    /// - `text`: The text that matched.
379	    /// - `captures`: An array containing a string for each matched capturing
380	    ///   group. The first item of the array contains the first matched
381	    ///   capturing, not the whole match! This is empty unless the `pattern` was
382	    ///   a regex with capturing groups.
